    <title>Warfare</title>
    <link href="https://otsuka.haus/reviews/2025-04-11-warfare/" />
    <updated>2025-04-11T00:00:00Z</updated>
    <id>https://otsuka.haus/reviews/2025-04-11-warfare/</id>
    <content type="html">&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;90 minutes of pure combat, no cuts, no exposition, no preaching. i thought we were getting a rah america movie but this was something else.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;sound design is incredible. the first show of force scene’s sound takes your breath away, the gunshots and explosions are disorienting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;really puts you in the mindset of what these guys must have gone through. you never want to be in that situation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</content>
